rComments: One of the few good actuarial science instructors at our department that doesn't try to push down grades or follow the department's controlled course average of C grade. 2nd midterm was difficult but his final exam was very fair which helped us out in the end.

Prof. Rian is a very good prof. He explains everything very clearly in lectures so you must attend them. Problem sets and tests can be tough but they are fair. If you have any problems, just ask the prof. he is very kind and will try his best to help.

Professor Dewji is exceptional. I have never had a professor that is so caring, approachable and smart, all at the same time. You can literally have a question about the material or about anything els and he will do his best to help you. The course is very very well taught and he is very fair with marking. He makes U of T worth it!
